## The GMV Scaling Trap

This is the critical detail most Triple Whale pricing pages don't emphasize.

### How It Works

1. You sign up when your store does $1M/year GMV. Cost: ~$549/mo.
2. Your store grows to $5M/year (great!). Cost: ~$1,129/mo.
3. Your store hits $10M/year. Cost: ~$2,000+/mo.

You're getting the **same features** at every GMV level. The only thing that changed is your revenue. Triple Whale charges more because your business grew — not because they're delivering more value.

### The Math

| GMV Growth | Price Increase | Same Features? |
|------------|---------------|---------------|
| $1M → $5M (5x growth) | ~$549 → ~$1,129 (~2x) | Yes |
| $1M → $10M (10x growth) | ~$549 → ~$2,000+ (~4x) | Yes |
| $1M → $25M (25x growth) | ~$549 → ~$3,500+ (~6x) | Yes |

### Why This Matters

The GMV trap means your attribution costs scale with revenue, not with value delivered. At $10M+ GMV, you're paying $2,000-3,500/month for the same dashboard that a $1M brand gets for $549/month.

Compare this to flat-tier pricing where you pay the same regardless of revenue growth.

