## 5 Alternatives Without GMV Scaling

### Pricing Comparison Table

| Platform | Free Tier | Entry Paid | Pricing Model | Best For |
|----------|-----------|------------|---------------|----------|
| **Northbeam** | No | $999/mo | Pageviews | DTC ML attribution |
| **Cometly** | No | ~$500/mo | Ad spend | Ad optimization |
| **mbuzz** | Yes | $29/mo | Flat tiers | Model flexibility |
| **Hyros** | No | ~$199/mo | Revenue | High-ticket / info products |
| **GA4** | Yes (free) | N/A | Free | Basic analytics |

*Full disclosure: mbuzz is our product. We've included it as one option among several.*

### 1. Northbeam — ML Attribution for DTC ($999/mo)

Northbeam uses ML-powered fractional attribution that prevents overcounting. Pageview-based pricing (not GMV). Includes creative analytics on the Professional tier.

**Why consider over Triple Whale:** No GMV scaling trap. ML prevents overcounting (sums to 100%). Creative analytics included. Better for brands $10M+ where Triple Whale gets expensive.

**Why stick with Triple Whale:** Triple Whale is cheaper at lower GMV brackets. Better Shopify integration. Moby AI recommendations are more actionable for non-technical teams.

Read more: [Northbeam Pricing](/articles/northbeam-pricing)

### 2. Cometly — Ad Platform Optimization (~$500/mo)

Cometly focuses on ad platform optimization with CAPI enrichment and AI recommendations. Ad-spend-based pricing.

**Why consider over Triple Whale:** Stronger CAPI enrichment for Meta match rates. AI Ads Manager for campaign optimization. Covers non-Shopify platforms.

**Why stick with Triple Whale:** Triple Whale is more comprehensive (email/SMS, affiliate, product analytics). Better Shopify-native experience.

Read more: [Cometly Pricing](/articles/cometly-pricing)

### 3. mbuzz — Flat Pricing at $29-299/mo

mbuzz offers 7 attribution models with custom rules and server-side tracking. Flat tiers — your price doesn't change as revenue grows. *Full disclosure: mbuzz is our product.*

| mbuzz Tier | Price | Records |
|------------|-------|---------|
| Free | $0 | <%= free_event_limit_display %> |
| Starter | $29/mo | 1M |
| Growth | $99/mo | 5M |
| Pro | $299/mo | 25M |

**Why consider over Triple Whale:** No GMV scaling trap. 7 attribution models vs Triple Whale's standard MTA. Custom attribution rules. Server-side tracking captures 30-40% more than client-side pixels.

**Why stick with Triple Whale:** Triple Whale has deeper Shopify integration, creative insights, RFM audiences, and AI recommendations (Moby). Better for Shopify-first brands who want an all-in-one platform.

### 4. Hyros — High-Ticket Attribution (~$199/mo)

Hyros specializes in high-ticket and info product attribution with call tracking and long cookie windows.

**Why consider over Triple Whale:** Better for high-ticket ($500+) products, info products, and coaching. Call tracking included. Revenue-based pricing.

**Why stick with Triple Whale:** Triple Whale is better for standard e-commerce with high SKU counts and lower AOV.

### 5. GA4 — Free

Google Analytics 4 is free and includes basic attribution. Not a Triple Whale replacement, but a starting point.

**Why consider over Triple Whale:** Free. Immediate setup. Useful for pre-revenue or bootstrapped stores.

**Why stick with Triple Whale:** GA4 has no e-commerce-specific attribution, no creative insights, no AI recommendations.

